genresAdvancedInfo.name: marimba mexicana
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Marimba Mexicana is a traditional Mexican music genre that features the marimba, a percussion instrument made of wooden bars struck with mallets. The music is lively and upbeat, often played at celebrations and festivals. Marimba Mexicana incorporates elements of indigenous Mexican music, Spanish influences, and African rhythms.
